.TH "doc_hamming_ecc_init" 9 "doc_hamming_ecc_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
doc_hamming_ecc_init \- Initialize hardware Hamming ECC engine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" doc_hamming_ecc_init
.BI "(struct docg3 *docg3 "  ","
.BI "int nb_bytes "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "docg3" 12
the device
.IP "nb_bytes" 12
the number of bytes covered by the ECC (Hamming covered)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function programs the ECC hardware to compute the hamming code on the
last provided N bytes to the hardware generator.
